# Frontend Chat UI

## Identity

This is the **public-facing** Litecoin Knowledge Hub chat interface, served at `chat.lite.space/chat`. End users interact with the RAG assistant through this UI. It is NOT the admin dashboard.

## Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Framework | Next.js | 15.5.8 |
| React | React | 19 |
| UI Components | Shadcn UI | configured (`components.json` present) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | v4 |
| Animation | Framer Motion | latest |
| Markdown | react-markdown | latest |
| Rich Text | TipTap | (for CMS article editor in `components/cms/`) |
| Validation | Zod + react-hook-form | latest |

## Key Conventions

### Component Library

Shadcn UI components live in `components/ui/`. To add a new component:

```bash
npx shadcn-ui@latest add <component-name>
```

Do NOT hand-roll components that Shadcn provides. Do NOT copy Shadcn patterns into `admin-frontend/` â€” it uses bare Radix without Shadcn.

### Routing & Base Path

The app uses `basePath: '/chat'` in `next.config.ts`. All internal links and API calls are relative to this base path. Never hardcode absolute URLs to the backend.

### API Communication

Next.js rewrites proxy API calls to the backend:

```
/api/v1/:path* â†’ ${BACKEND_URL}/api/v1/:path*
```

Always use relative fetch paths like `/api/v1/chat/stream`. The backend URL is resolved by the rewrite config, not by client code.

### Streaming Protocol

Chat responses use `ReadableStream` + `TextDecoder` with SSE-style JSON lines:

```
data: {"status": "thinking", ...}\n
data: {"status": "streaming", "chunk": "chunk..."}\n
data: {"status": "follow_ups", "questions": [...]}\n
data: {"status": "complete", ...}\n
```

Event types to handle: `thinking`, `streaming`, `follow_ups`, `complete`, `error`, `usage_status`, `blockchain_data`. (Legacy clients may ignore a `sources` event if ever reintroduced.)

On 403 `invalid_challenge`, fetch a new challenge from `/api/v1/auth/challenge` and retry once.

### Authentication

The public frontend uses **fingerprint challenge-response** for rate limiting â€” NOT Bearer tokens. Auth flow:

1. `GET /api/v1/auth/challenge` â†’ receive challenge
2. Include `X-Fingerprint` header on subsequent requests

There is no login page, no user accounts, no `localStorage` tokens in this frontend.

### Content Sources

- **Suggested questions**: Fetched from Payload CMS REST API at `NEXT_PUBLIC_PAYLOAD_URL/api/suggested-questions`
- **Chat responses**: Streamed from backend via `/api/v1/chat/stream`

### CMS Components

`components/cms/` contains an article editor (TipTap-based) with `ArticleEditor.tsx`, `FrontmatterForm.tsx`, `TiptapEditor.tsx`. These are part of the public frontend for content contribution workflows.

## Forbidden

- Never import from `admin-frontend/` â€” these are completely separate applications
- Never use Bearer token auth patterns â€” that is admin-only
- Never hardcode `localhost:8000` or any backend URL in client code
- Never use `getServerSideProps` patterns from older Next.js â€” this is App Router (Next.js 15)
